Yes Decurrent / Bluntly Attached | Whitish Decurrent Volva Volva / Rooting / None | Often swollen in the middle, somewhat rooting. Large | Veil: Yes | Tough. Ring prominant and double. Odor and taste are mild or slightly unpleasant. Not mealy. Flesh is white and hard. Tricholoma caligatum group do not have decurrent gills, no double ring, and are sometimes under hardwoods. Tricholoma murrillianum group are similar, but whiter and have a spicy odor. Catathelasma ventricosum

Small Depressed Depressed / Striate / None | Blocky or squarish at first, then convex with possible sunken center, striate. Tacky when fresh but soon dry. Bald. Medium Slimy or Sticky Slimy or Sticky / None | Ovate when young, becoming convex or flat. always viscid to gelatinous when fresh and is white, grey, or grey-brown. No Free | White becoming pinkish. Close or nearly crowded, short gills frequent Free Volva Volva / None | White volva at base. Base slightly swollen. disColoring brownish. Medium / Large | Veil: No | Flesh white, not changing when sliced. Odor not distinctive or slightly foul. When gills are white some Amanitas can look similar. Spore print will show the distinction.
